mediaNotes: male bluebird singing and moving between perches. Good sound but airplane noise
Sitting high in a cottonwood above the picnic area. Interrupted by a car.

Predator warning calls by the adult(s) tending their fledged young. I had not seen the adult female but she likely was present and probably calling with the male in this recording. I have heard them give these call when a bird of prey or other threat is seen. Also see ML176629481 recording of Sept 10th of similar calls by the same  birds.
